name: XmlStreamReader
description: The XmlStreamReader class provides methods for forward, read-only access to XML data. You can pull data from XML or skip unwanted events. You can parse nested XML content thatâ€™s up to 50 nodes deep.

getattributecount().name: getAttributeCount
getattributecount().description: Returns the number of attributes on the start element, excluding namespace definitions.

getattributelocalname(integer).name: getAttributeLocalName
getattributelocalname(integer).description: Returns the local name of the attribute at the specified index.

getattributenamespace(integer).name: getAttributeNamespace
getattributenamespace(integer).description: Returns the namespace URI of the attribute at the specified index.

getattributeprefix(integer).name: getAttributePrefix
getattributeprefix(integer).description: Returns the prefix of this attribute at the specified index.

getattributetype(integer).name: getAttributeType
getattributetype(integer).description: Returns the XML type of the attribute at the specified index.

getattributevalue(string,string).name: getAttributeValue
getattributevalue(string,string).signature: public String getAttributeValue(String namespaceUri, String localName)
getattributevalue(string,string).overrideSignature: public override String getAttributeValue(String namespaceUri, String localName)
getattributevalue(string,string).description: Returns the value of the attribute in the specified localName at the specified URI.

getattributevalueat(integer).name: getAttributeValueAt
getattributevalueat(integer).description: Returns the value of the attribute at the specified index.

geteventtype().name: getEventType
geteventtype().description: Returns the type of XML event the cursor is pointing to.

getlocalname().name: getLocalName
getlocalname().description: Returns the local name of the current event.

getlocation().name: getLocation
getlocation().description: Return the current location of the cursor.

getnamespace().name: getNamespace
getnamespace().description: If the current event is a start element or end element, this method returns the URI of the prefix or the default namespace.

getnamespacecount().name: getNamespaceCount
getnamespacecount().description: Returns the number of namespaces declared on a start element or end element.

getnamespaceprefix(integer).name: getNamespacePrefix
getnamespaceprefix(integer).description: Returns the prefix for the namespace declared at the index.

getnamespaceuri(string).name: getNamespaceURI
getnamespaceuri(string).description: Return the URI for the given prefix.

getnamespaceuriat(integer).name: getNamespaceURIAt
getnamespaceuriat(integer).description: Returns the URI for the namespace declared at the index.

getpidata().name: getPIData
getpidata().description: Returns the data section of a processing instruction.

getpitarget().name: getPITarget
getpitarget().description: Returns the target section of a processing instruction.

getprefix().name: getPrefix
getprefix().description: Returns the prefix of the current XML event or null if the event does not have a prefix.

gettext().name: getText
gettext().description: Returns the current value of the XML event as a string.

getversion().name: getVersion
getversion().description: Returns the XML version specified on the XML declaration. Returns null if none was declared.

hasname().name: hasName
hasname().description: Returns true if the current XML event has a name. Returns false otherwise.

hasnext().name: hasNext
hasnext().description: Returns true if there are more  XML events and false if there are no more XML events.

hastext().name: hasText
hastext().description: Returns true if the current event has text, false otherwise.

ischaracters().name: isCharacters
ischaracters().description: Returns true if the cursor points to a character data XML event. Otherwise, returns false.

isendelement().name: isEndElement
isendelement().description: Returns true if the cursor points to an end tag. Otherwise, it returns false.

isstartelement().name: isStartElement
isstartelement().description: Returns true if the cursor points to a start tag. Otherwise, it returns false.

iswhitespace().name: isWhiteSpace
iswhitespace().description: Returns true if the cursor points to a character data XML event that consists of all white space. Otherwise it returns false.

next().name: next
next().description: Reads the next XML event. A processor may return all contiguous character data in a single chunk, or it may split it into several chunks. Returns an integer which indicates the type of event.

nexttag().name: nextTag
nexttag().description: Skips any white space (the isWhiteSpace method returns true), comment, or processing instruction XML events, until a start element or end element is reached. Returns the index for that XML event.

setcoalescing(boolean).name: setCoalescing
setcoalescing(boolean).description: If you specify true for returnAsSingleBlock, text is returned in a single block, from a start element to the first end element or the next start element, whichever comes first. If you specify it as false, the parser may return text in multiple blocks.

setnamespaceaware(boolean).name: setNamespaceAware
setnamespaceaware(boolean).description: If you specify true for isNamespaceAware, the parser recognizes namespace. If you specify it as false, the parser does not. The default value is true.

tostring().name: toString
tostring().description: Returns a string containing the length of the input XML given to XmlStreamReader and the first 50 characters of the input XML.

xmlstreamreader(string).name: XmlStreamReader
xmlstreamreader(string).description: Creates a new instance of the XmlStreamReader class for the specified XML input.
